result.execSummary:
The defendant Melissa L Ozleplebici was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Melissa L Ozleplebici is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Melissa L Ozleplebici was found guilty of Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

9:00 AM - No appearance by Def - Atty Sean William O'Neill present.  Emily E. Hynek appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Crt: I have to say I was surprised at the original mtn as I couldn't gather from the mtn what was the issue here. In your response that there are 2 issues, the reliability of the dog and the other is the stop. 
O'Neill: also the issue of illegal detention is in there, what was reasonable under Tobias. 
Hynek: none of that was noticed in the origial mtn. I should have been given time to speak w/ the canine officer and he indicates this  was an issue since Feb. Nothing in the response to dispute what's in the original report, no aff from the def and no case law that the officer couldn't stop her for those violations. 
Crt: I was sympathetic to the mtn to quash when I read the original mtn and that didn't lay out the legal theories that were at issue. I will acccept the response to the State's mtn to quash as an addendum as it lays out the theories at issue. As to the stop the def is being asked to disprove a neg and the state is put on notice that the basis for the stop is at issue along w/ the ? of whether the detention was unreasonabley prolonged to allow the dog sniff and the reliability is being put at issue as well.
